text: My to go place for Economic Bee Hoon. A variety of choices: fried bee hoon (dark and white), kway teow mee, kway teow, fried instant noodles, Hokkein mee, mee goreng etc. Also serves nasi lemak. Tried all of them and they have the just right taste. Another star is the fried chicken wings, usually need a 2nd batch for the lunch crowd.
